OL,3,CWho is Lindsay Whittle? Caerphilly's
OL,4,Cnew MS who's fought 18 elections
OL,6,FIt's the 18th election he's fought for
OL,7,Feither the UK Parliament or Welsh
OL,8,FSenedd. He's stood in every Welsh
OL,9,Felection since the devolved Government
OL,10,Fwas first formed in 1999.
OL,12,FIn his victory speech he joked,
OL,13,F"Ladies and Gentlemen, you'll forgive
OL,14,Fme. I'm not used to speaking first in
OL,15,Fthese election counts."
OL,17,FWhen he first stood for a UK General
OL,18,FElection in 1983, he received just 13%
OL,19,Fof the vote. The seat went to Labour.
OL,20,FThe election was a landslide for the
OL,21,FConservatives and Margaret Thatcher.
